<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Single specimen, ~ 12 cm tall, narrow sea pen; in situ colouration orange with whitish polyps (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Protoptilum stet. CCZ _ 068 A in situ image B whole colony C detail of polyps before preservation. Scale bars: 1 cm (A); 5 mm (B); 2 mm (C). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (B, C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716345" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">19A</figureCitation>
). Two rows, opposite to each other, of elongated polyp calyces along the rachis (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Protoptilum stet. CCZ _ 068 A in situ image B whole colony C detail of polyps before preservation. Scale bars: 1 cm (A); 5 mm (B); 2 mm (C). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (B, C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716345" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">19B, C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
