<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</emphasis>
Single specimen, unattached, tube-dweller with tentacles extended above the sediment in situ (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figure 21. Spirularia stet. CCZ _ 067 A in situ image B specimen before preservation. Scale bars: 1 cm (A); 2 mm (B). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716347" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">21A</figureCitation>
). Very long, conical, tapering, reddish brown tentacles; capitulum whitish when alive (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figure 21. Spirularia stet. CCZ _ 067 A in situ image B specimen before preservation. Scale bars: 1 cm (A); 2 mm (B). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716347" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">21A</figureCitation>
). Column is 12 mm in height and 5 mm in width excluding tentacles (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figure 21. Spirularia stet. CCZ _ 067 A in situ image B specimen before preservation. Scale bars: 1 cm (A); 2 mm (B). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716347" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">21B</figureCitation>
). Tube consisting of soft sediment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The closest matches to the COI and 16S sequences were sequences from other members of the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Milne Edwards &amp; Haime" authorityYear="1851" class="Anthozoa" family="Cerianthidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Spirularia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Cerianthidae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName genus="Pachycenrianthus" lsidName="Pachycenrianthus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pachycenrianthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Delle Chiaje" authorityYear="1841" class="Anthozoa" family="Cerianthidae" genus="Cerianthus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cerianthus" order="Spirularia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cerianthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="Ceriantheromorphe" lsidName="Ceriantheromorphe" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ceriantheromorphe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, in the concatenated phylogeny, it forms a clade with 
<taxonomicName genus="Boctrunidifer" lsidName="Boctrunidifer" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Boctrunidifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 1 and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Agassiz" baseAuthorityYear="1864" class="Anthozoa" family="Cerianthidae" genus="Ceriantheopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ceriantheopsis americanus" order="Ceriantharia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="americanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ceriantheopsis americanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, belonging to the families 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carlgren" authorityYear="1912" class="Anthozoa" family="Botrucnidiferidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Spirularia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Botrucnidiferidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Milne Edwards &amp; Haime" authorityYear="1851" class="Anthozoa" family="Cerianthidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Spirularia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Cerianthidae</taxonomicName>
, respectively (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Rooted Bayesian phylogeny of Ceriantharia. Concatenated (12 S, 16 S, 18 S, 28 S, and COI) median consensus BEAST tree with posterior probability (PP) and bootstrap (BS) values indicated. Only values of PP&gt; 0.70 and BS&gt; 50 are shown, with values of PP&gt; 0.95 and BS&gt; 90 indicated with a circle. Nodes not recovered on the RAxML tree are indicated with a hyphen. Sequences generated in this study are highlighted in violet." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716346" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">20</figureCitation>
). As 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1093/zoolinnean/zlz158" author="Forero-Mejia, AC" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="397 - 416" refId="B28" refString="Forero-Mejia, AC, Molodtsova, T, Oestman, C, Bavestrello, G, Rouse, GW, 2019. Molecular phylogeny of Ceriantharia (Cnidaria: Anthozoa) reveals non-monophyly of traditionally accepted families. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 190 (2): 397 - 416, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1093/zoolinnean/zlz158" title="Molecular phylogeny of Ceriantharia (Cnidaria: Anthozoa) reveals non-monophyly of traditionally accepted families." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/zoolinnean/zlz158" volume="190" year="2019">Forero-Mejia et al. (2019)</bibRefCitation>
recovered both families as non-monophyletic and a revision of these is suggested, we were unable to assign it to a family.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology.</emphasis>
The specimen was found buried in the sediment on a seamount in APEI 7, at 3132 m depth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Comparison with image-based catalogue.</emphasis>
A very similar 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carlgren" authorityYear="1912" class="Anthozoa" genus="Ceriantheopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Ceriantharia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="order">Ceriantharia</taxonomicName>
morphotype (i.e., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="den Hartog" authorityYear="1977" class="Asteroidea" genus="Spirularia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Spirularia" order="Brisingida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Spirularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. indet., CER_001) has been commonly encountered in seabed image surveys conducted across the eastern CCZ, always found semi-buried with the tentacles extending above the sediment surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Class 
<taxonomicName authorityName="den Hartog" authorityYear="1977" class="Scyphozoa" genus="Spirularia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Brisingida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="class">Scyphozoa</taxonomicName>
Goette, 1887
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
For the class 
<taxonomicName authorityName="den Hartog" authorityYear="1977" class="Scyphozoa" genus="Spirularia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Brisingida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="class">Scyphozoa</taxonomicName>
, there are currently 128 records from&gt; 3000 m depth in the CCZ, but none represent preserved specimens (
<bibRefCitation author="O'Loughlin, PM" journalOrPublisher="Part II, Topical Studies in Oceanography" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B75" refString="OBIS (2022) Ocean Biodiversity Information System. Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission of UNESCO." year="2011">OBIS 2022</bibRefCitation>
). We collected a single specimen, for which the sequence for the COI gene was successfully amplified and included in a multi-gene phylogeny (16S, 18S, 28S, and COI) of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="den Hartog" authorityYear="1977" class="Scyphozoa" genus="Spirularia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Brisingida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="class">Scyphozoa</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Rooted Bayesian phylogeny of Scyphozoa. Concatenated (16 S, 18 S, 28 S, and COI) median consensus BEAST tree with posterior probability (PP) and bootstrap (BS) values indicated. Only values of PP&gt; 0.70 and BS&gt; 50 are shown, with values of PP&gt; 0.95 and BS&gt; 90 indicated with a circle. Nodes not recovered on the RAxML tree are indicated with a hyphen. Sequences generated in this study are highlighted in violet." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716348" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
