Single specimen, ~ 4.5 cm in diameter; with transparent bell and light brown tentacles in situ (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Ulmaridae stet. CCZ _ 069 A in situ image B specimen before preservation C rhopalia. Scale bars: 1 cm (A); 5 mm (B). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (B, C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716349" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">23A</figureCitation>
). Rhopalia are evident around the bell (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Ulmaridae stet. CCZ _ 069 A in situ image B specimen before preservation C rhopalia. Scale bars: 1 cm (A); 5 mm (B). Image attribution: Durden and Smith (A); Wiklund, Durden, Drennan, and McQuaid (B, C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1113.82172.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/716349" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">23B, C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
